The Nigerian Army on Saturday said that the troops of the Operation Desert Sanity have uncovered the carcass of the missing Alpha Jet of the Nigerian Air Force (NAF) in Sambisa Forest, Borno State. It could be recalled that the Alpha fighter jet, marked NAF 475 went missing almost a year ago after losing radar contact with the air force base in Maiduguri. Making the announcement in a brief statement issued on it’s verified Twitter page, the Nigerian Army said that the troops discover the wreckage while on a clearance patrol in Sambisa Forest. The statement read, “Troops of Operation Desert Sanity on clearance patrol in Sambisa Forest, Borno State, have uncovered the wreckage of crashed Alpha Jet aircraft (NAF475) that went off the radar with two crew members on 31 March 2021. The statement added, “Further exploitation (is) ongoing.”